This project adapts design and prompt text from Hermes Agent by Nous Research
(https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent), used under the MIT License.

Specifically, the following are derived from Hermes Agent:
  - The bounded, §-delimited two-store memory model (USER.md / MEMORY.md) and
    its character limits (1375 / 2200), ported in plugins/mnemo/bin/mnemo-mem.
  - The background-review judgment guidance (what to save, the skill preference
    order, the "do not capture" list), adapted in
    plugins/mnemo/prompts/combined-review.md.

Hermes Agent's implementation is a Python agent runtime; mnemo is an independent
re-implementation of the *loop* as native Claude Code plugin hooks, and shares
no source code — only the design and prompt guidance noted above.
